1967–73: The now-defunct Project MINARET was created to spy on U.S. citizens. At the request of the U.S. Army, those who protested against the Vietnam War were put on the NSA's "watch list".<ref name="pbs"/>
File:Church Committee report (Book II).pdf|thumb|The Church Committee of the United States Senate published the final report on "'':File:Church Committee report (Book II).pdf|Intelligence Activities and the Rights of Americans''" in 1976 (PDF, 26.54 MB)
File:Walt Disney Snow white 1937 trailer screenshot (13).jpg|thumb|From 1940 until his death in 1966, the American business magnate Walt Disney served as a "S.A.C. Contact" (trusted informant) for the U.S. government to weed out communists and dissidents from the Show business|entertainment industry, according to documents obtained by ''The New York Times''.<ref>cite news|last=MITGANG|first=HERBERT|title=Disney Link To the F.B.I. And Hoover Is Disclosed|url=https://www.nytimes.com/1993/05/06/movies/disney-link-to-the-fbi-and-hoover-is-disclosed.html|publisher=''The New York Times''|accessdate=19 September 2013|date=6 May 1993</ref>
